  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6571.87 sitting between the GEX flip at 6550 and max positive gamma at 6580, dealers are currently in moderate selling mode as they hedge their long gamma positions against the ongoing rally. The thick positive GEX wall at 6580 (+14.3B) should act as strong resistance with dealers ramping up selling pressure as spot approaches, while the regime suggests mean reversion back toward 6550-6565 is likely. Watch for accelerated dealer selling if we push through 6580 toward the next major wall at 6590, but any dip below 6565 should trigger dealer buying that supports the downside.",
